The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of users in a community-based question answering platform, which involves social interactions and content moderation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Retrieval sub-categories (cs.SI and cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of network properties to detect abusive users, which could fall under the Social Computing sub-category (cs.SOC). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze user contributions, which could relate to the Computational Linguistics sub-category (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of respecting community rules and the role of user contributions, which could relate to the Cybersecurity sub-category (cs.CYBER).
